        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "purpose": "describing",
          "value": "`Ideal.span_singleton_prime` gives `IsPrime (span {p}) ↔ Prime p` in any commutative ring; combined with `isPrime_bot` for `NoZeroDivisors`, this classifies the prime ideals of `ℤ` as `(p)` and `(0)`.",
          "format": "text/plain"
        }
      ],
      "target": {
        "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_ideal?oldid=1356076440",
        "selector": {
          "type": "TextQuoteSelector",
          "exact": "The prime ideals for the integers are the sets that contain all the multiples of a given prime number, together with the zero ideal",
          "prefix": " ring of integers . [ 1 ] [ 2 ] ",
          "suffix": " . Primitive ideals are prime, a"
        }
      }
    },
