        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "purpose": "describing",
          "value": "`IsPrime.isPrimary` and `IsPrime.isRadical` (in `Mathlib.RingTheory.Ideal.Operations`) give the primary and semiprime/radical parts. Mathlib has no notion of `primitive ideal` (annihilator of a simple module) for noncommutative rings, so the first conjunct is not formalized.",
          "format": "text/plain"
        }
      ],
      "target": {
        "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_ideal?oldid=1356076440",
        "selector": {
          "type": "TextQuoteSelector",
          "exact": "Primitive ideals are prime, and prime ideals are both primary and semiprime",
          "prefix": " together with the zero ideal . ",
          "suffix": " . An ideal P of a commutative r"
        }
      }
    },
