        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "purpose": "describing",
          "value": "Mathlib's `class Ideal.IsPrime` has fields `ne_top'` (P ≠ R) and `mem_or_mem'` (x*y ∈ P → x ∈ P ∨ y ∈ P), and `isPrime_iff` gives the conjunction form. This matches Wikipedia's two-property definition verbatim (and works for any semiring).",
          "format": "text/plain"
        }
      ],
      "target": {
        "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_ideal?oldid=1356076440",
        "selector": {
          "type": "TextQuoteSelector",
          "exact": "An ideal P of a commutative ring R is prime if it has the following two properties",
          "prefix": "re both primary and semiprime . ",
          "suffix": ": If a and b are two elements of"
