        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "purpose": "describing",
          "value": "Mathlib's `Ideal.IsPrime` uses the elementwise commutative form (`x*y ∈ P → x ∈ P ∨ y ∈ P`), and there is no two-sided-ideal `AB ⊆ P → A ⊆ P ∨ B ⊆ P` definition for noncommutative rings (the file's own TODO notes this gap).",
          "format": "text/plain"
        }
      ],
      "target": {
